# Wheat and Whisper Farm Website

A beautiful, nostalgic website for Wheat and Whisper Farm - where wild hearts find grace on the prairie.

## üåæ About

This website showcases the farm, horses, and handcrafted products with a warm, earthy aesthetic inspired by slow living and traditional craftsmanship.

## üöÄ Quick Start - GitHub Pages Deployment

### Step 1: Create a GitHub Repository

1. Go to [GitHub](https://github.com) and sign in (or create an account)
2. Click the "+" icon in the top right, then "New repository"
3. Name your repository (e.g., `wheat-and-whisper-farm`)
4. Make it **Public** (required for free GitHub Pages)
5. Click "Create repository"

### Step 2: Upload Your Files

**Option A: Using GitHub Web Interface**
1. In your new repository, click "uploading an existing file"
2. Drag and drop all files from this folder:
   - `index.html`
   - `styles.css`
   - `script.js`
   - `WheatandWhisperLogo.png`
   - `README.md`
3. Scroll down and click "Commit changes"

**Option B: Using Git Command Line**
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: Wheat and Whisper Farm website"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/YOUR-REPO-NAME.git
git push -u origin main
```

### Step 3: Enable GitHub Pages

1. Go to your repository on GitHub
2. Click **Settings** (top menu)
3. Click **Pages** (left sidebar)
4. Under "Branch," select **main** and **/root**
5. Click **Save**
6. Wait 2-3 minutes for deployment

Your site will be live at:
`https://YOUR-USERNAME.github.io/YOUR-REPO-NAME/`

## üìù Customization Guide

### Update Content

Edit `index.html` to customize:
- Farm story and about text
- Contact information
- Social media links
- Newsletter signup action

### Change Colors

Edit `styles.css` - Look for the `:root` section at the top:
```css
:root {
    --wheat: #C9A66B;
    --earth-brown: #8B6F47;
    --deep-brown: #5D4E37;
    /* ... more colors ... */
}
```

### Add Photos

1. Add your photos to the repository
2. Replace image placeholders in `index.html`:
   ```html
   <div class="image-placeholder">
   ```
   Change to:
   ```html
   <img src="your-photo.jpg" alt="Description">
   ```

### Update Logo

Replace `WheatandWhisperLogo.png` with your updated logo (keep the same filename, or update the path in `index.html`).

